import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='Beak_Length__mm_', y='Beak_Depth__mm_', hue='Species')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of beak length and depth among different species?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="Sex", y="Body_Mass__g_", data=data)
    chart.axhline(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Flipper_Length__mm_', hue='Species', multiple='stack', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['Flipper_Length__mm_'].median(), color='black', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Flipper_Length__mm_'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flipper length among different species?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
